1
00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:10,240
That girl over there,

2
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:12,000
it's her first day at work today,

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,920
and she already got kicked out by a customer.

4
00:00:13,920 --> 00:00:15,720
She's already in a place like this,

5
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:17,780
but still acts like an innocent lady.

6
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,280
I hate hypocrites like her.

7
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:21,400
Exactly.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,480
Girls, don't learn from her.

9
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:25,280
Do you hear me?

10
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:27,400
Got it, Linda.

11
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:31,130
What are you doing hiding here?

12
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Not bad.

13
00:00:40,840 --> 00:00:41,720
Stop.

14
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:46,000
I'm sorry, Linda.

15
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:48,780
Do you know whose seat this is?

16
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,680
I saw you had a lot of customers today,

17
00:00:52,680 --> 00:00:55,840
and thought you wouldn't be back for a while,

18
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:57,200
so I borrowed it.

19
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,200
What do you mean?

20
00:00:58,520 --> 00:01:00,520
You can use my seat when I'm not here?

21
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,260
I didn't mean that.

22
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:06,400
I'm not a petty person,

23
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:08,640
but I'm afraid.

24
00:01:12,880 --> 00:01:13,680
Tacky.

25
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:16,039
Let me go.

26
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:17,640
You filthy hick.

27
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:19,080
Don't think I'm afraid of you.

28
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:20,000
I'm telling you,

29
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:22,440
you won't get a single penny from me today.

30
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,800
Jiajia, untie me.

31
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,200
Jiajia.

32
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:29,200
I knew you were a bitch.

33
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:30,920
You're just like him.

34
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:32,720
You two pieces of trash.

35
00:01:32,720 --> 00:01:34,400
You're not even fit to tie my shoes.

36
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:35,400
Just wait till I get out.

37
00:01:35,400 --> 00:01:36,460
Wait till I get out.

38
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,840
It's fine. They are my two brothers.

39
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:03,480
Mr. Zhang.

40
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:05,520
Long time no see, Captain Ma.

41
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,320
Sorry to trouble you, Mr. Zhang.

42
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:08,680
Don't mention it.

43
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:10,199
As you requested,

44
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:11,840
the files of those imprisoned during the crackdown a few years ago

45
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,560
and who fit the crime profile,

46
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:14,960
are all prepared for you.

47
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:17,800
What about this month?

48
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:19,760
Are there any newly reported persons of interest?

49
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:20,880
Actually, no.

50
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,280
Are they all behaving so well?

51
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,600
They are quite well-behaved.

52
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,000
How is your Yinuo doing?

53
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:26,960
She must be in elementary school now, right?

54
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:27,880
Is everything alright?

55
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:29,280
She is fine. Pretty good.

56
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,560
Got a light, buddy?

57
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:53,560
By the way.

58
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:55,400
What do you think of this guy?

59
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,079
Did he come?

60
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:57,360
He came last week.

61
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,000
What's he like in person?

62
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,080
He's pretty honest.

63
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:02,200
Maybe he's gotten older and wiser.

64
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:04,490
He works at an auto repair shop now.

65
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:07,760
I guess he can finally settle down.

66
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:08,890
An auto repair shop?

67
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:11,810
Come and visit often. 6231.

68
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,600
We can't afford it.

69
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:20,480
Where do you live?

70
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:23,400
These two are my coworkers. We live at the auto repair shop.

71
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:26,680
It's far. My girlfriend works inside.

72
00:03:27,079 --> 00:03:29,880
I came to pick her up from work and get a midnight snack.

73
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:32,280
Is it the one at the corner in the south of the city?

74
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,520
Yes, that's the one.

75
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:35,320
Okay.

76
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:41,680
Where are you going?

77
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,540
To investigate a case. Take this.

78
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:45,079
What is this?

79
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,160
These are the most suspicious released prisoners

80
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:48,320
that I've screened.

81
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:50,040
Take it.

82
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:55,650
What about my second-class merit?

83
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:57,400
What? I'm on a diet.

84
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,000
Brother.

85
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:14,520
Come in.

86
00:04:20,519 --> 00:04:21,720
Dyed your hair blond.

87
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:23,480
Don't mess it up.

88
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,920
Call her sister-in-law.

89
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,530
Sister-in-law.

90
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:33,020
Have you two eaten?

91
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,480
Not yet.

92
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,120
It's been a while since you had my noodles.

93
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:36,920
Stop talking.

94
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:37,880
I'll make two bowls for you.

95
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,480
Okay. Thank you, Brother.

96
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,400
Chat with your sister-in-law.

97
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:41,600
Thank you, Brother.

98
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:45,440
Are you sure it's just the two of us?

99
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:48,560
After it's done, the two of us will fly away.

100
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:52,480
Hua Weihong, who exactly are you?

101
00:04:54,159 --> 00:04:56,090
See if my cooking has gotten worse.

102
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,560
It smells so good.

103
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,020
Still tastes the same.

104
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:06,300
What's wrong? Aren't you hungry?

105
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,660
I'm not hungry.

106
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:09,400
Eat a little.

107
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:15,720
Brother.

108
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:17,580
What does she mean?

109
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:18,650
Eat the noodles.

110
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,490
Eat the noodles.

111
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:45,560
Let me go.

112
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:49,400
I'm really scared.

113
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:53,120
Let me go.

114
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:55,600
Sister Na, don't worry.

115
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:56,840
He promised me.

116
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:59,000
We'll leave as soon as we get the money.

117
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,000
We won't hurt you.

118
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:02,720
He told me the same thing.

119
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,920
But I don't believe him.

120
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,920
I believe you.

121
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,200
I beg you.

122
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,320
I only believe you.

123
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:11,850
I only believe you, Jiajia.

124
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:17,680
Are you done eating?

125
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:22,360
Lao Er, let's get to work.

126
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:39,760
Didn't you say it would just be the two of us?

127
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,440
They've been following me since they were kids.

128
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:43,760
Wherever I go, they go.

129
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,500
I have to bring them along.

130
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:25,000
Second brother, is it my turn yet?

131
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,330
I'm getting impatient.

132
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,520
This thing is good for burning feet.

133
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:30,880
Can it burn a face?

134
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:31,920
It's the same.

135
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:33,940
Whatever, we'll know once we try.

136
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,440
Burn her.

137
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:41,159
What are you whimpering about?

138
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:45,000
What is it?

139
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:47,360
My bankbook password is on the table.

140
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:50,240
Boss.

141
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,530
You go get the money.

142
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:33,320
Me?

143
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:35,919
Boss.

144
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:37,679
She'll go.

145
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,440
I told you.

146
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:52,520
You're in charge of my money from now on.

147
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:56,880
Go at dawn.

148
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,000
Don't be nervous.

149
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:31,970
I don't like this smell.

150
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,240
Relax.

151
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,260
Do you still remember the PIN?

152
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:46,600
This is the last step.

153
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,280
Be quick.

154
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:08,640
Number Three.

155
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:11,800
Boss.

156
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:15,880
You two go in and take some photos of them.

157
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:18,400
Keep some leverage on hand.

158
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:20,800
So they won't cause trouble after we leave.

159
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:24,360
Taking photos? I'm good at that.

160
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:26,480
But Boss,

161
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,680
for the photos,

162
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:31,000
can I decide how to take them?

163
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:34,800
Number Two.

164
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:37,200
Boss said to listen to me.

165
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,600
Give it to me.

166
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:44,900
Let's go, Boss.

167
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,640
Let go.

168
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:14,200
Take your hand off.

169
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:23,240
Hello, I want to withdraw some money.

170
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:24,900
Please give me your bankbook.

171
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,880
How much do you want to withdraw?

172
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:38,800
40,000.

173
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:41,200
That's quite a lot.

174
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,580
Please enter your PIN.

175
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,400
Please wait a moment.

176
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:53,640
Police station.

177
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:04,520
I found it.

178
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:07,180
Linda made a large withdrawal from her account.

179
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:13,800
I'm not too sure about next month's escort schedule.

180
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:17,600
Come over tomorrow to verify it.

181
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:22,720
Wrong.

182
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:24,880
The PIN is incorrect.

183
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,850
Yes, please enter it again.

184
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:32,680
Here are the withdrawal records you asked for.

185
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:34,920
Do you remember who made the withdrawal?

186
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:35,920
It was a girl.

187
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:38,000
Was it this girl?

188
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:41,000
I can't remember clearly.

189
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,280
Check the city's large deposit records for the past two days.

190
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:47,080
Okay.

191
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:52,000
But who would steal money and then deposit it in a bank?

192
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:53,600
We have to try every possibility.
